citation.case_name: Dickinson v. First Nat. Bank of Homestead

html:
393 U.S. 409

89 S.Ct. 685

21 L.Ed.2d 634

Fred O. DICKINSON, Comptroller
v.
FIRST NATIONAL BANK OF HOMESTEAD et al.

No. 741.

Supreme Court of the United States

January 20, 1969

Rehearing Denied March 3, 1969.

See 393 U.S. 1124, 89 S.Ct. 988.

Earl Faircloth, Atty. Gen. of Florida, and Fred M. Burns and Larry Levy, Asst. Attys. Gen., for appellant.

O. Ralph Matousek, for appellee First National Bank of Homestead.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motion to affirm is granted and the judgment is affirmed.

2

Mr. Justice STEWART is of the opinion that probable jurisdiction should be noted.

3

Mr. Justice FORTAS took no part in the consideration or decision of this case.
